Package com.camerontec.util.pool

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    IDoublyLinkable<T>
    Interface to be implemented by any class which is capable of maintaining the standard linkage references for use in a doubly-linked list.
    IReference<T>
    Interface to be implemented by classes whose instances are capable of holding a reference some other object.
    IReferencePool<T>
    Interface to be implemented by objects capable of maintaining a pool of references, each referring to a concrete referent object.
    IReferentFactory<T>
    Interface to be implemented by classes capable of creating concrete referent instances.
    IReferentLifecycle<T>
    Interface that provides hooks for pool consumers to perform operations on referents during check-out and check-in.
    Recyclable
    Interface to be implemented by classes whose instances are capable of being recycled and used again.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    LinkedListOfPoolableReferences<T>
    A restricted linked list implementation of PoolableReferences which does not require object creation.
    PoolableReference<T>
    Poolable reference class.
    UnboundedReferencePool<T>
    An unbounded reference pool implementation which guarantees no garbage generation.
